<br>
Reason the A-Bombs were dropped on Japan was pretty complex.<br>
1) TO save the lives of probbaly hunreds of thousandso soldiers you beter freakin believe ANY leader with half a brain woudl have dropped the bombs.<br>
<br>
2) There wee plans to secretly ship captured german nerve gas to use on Japan if that was needed.<br>
<br>
3) Large part of why they were used was to do with preventing the Soviet Union taking over Japan and togive Stalin a clear warning.<br>
<br>
4) Although Japan was close to collapse, and there were hints of surrender being possible, Japan need *HAMMERED*. This is something a lot of folk won't talk about, but to put it bluntly, the Japanese due to centuries of isolation and then the insane government and its propaganda, had become nationally racist and arrogant to a terrible degree. <br>
  You have to understand that while the majority of German soldiers were not personally involved with the horrors that went on, a majority of the Japanese army *was*. At the end of World War 2, there was public desire for nuking Germany and Japan out of existance, folk were that disgusted and angry. So there was an element  of thinking that Jpaan needed to be *humbled*, it was not enough that dignified surrender happen, they had to be utterly CRUSHED and humiliated. Otherwise that arrogance and racism would not be checked.<br>
  if you think I'm talking crap you need to read up on the histories and personal experiences. While some Japanese protested about the horrors, particularly in the Navy, most whole heartedly went along with them, this was *intstitutionalized mass murder torture, rape, infanticide etc* It was not somtheing to be tolerated and frankly the Japanese military got off too damn lightly, and still HAVE.<br>
  The A-Bombing was to act as a slap to the nation's pride and arrogance.<br>
<br>
5) More folk died in one fire bomb raid in one night on Tokyo than died in both  Hiroshima and Nagasaki.<br>
<br>
6) It's one of the great, sad, bitter ironies of life that while the children there certainly did not deserve that fate, nor did many of the inhabitants, what the heck can you do to a *nation* to make them understand *personally* that war is horrible, that acts of horror on others *are* horror, and that someone who is not of your nationality is not inferior, except by causing absolute devastation? It would take decades, centuries of education to get that into folk, and by which time there may have ben another war started by them *points at Germany WW1 and WW2*<br>
<br>
7) WHile it's fine now for folk to say &quot;Yeah they woudl have surrendered&quot;, that's with hindsight and that may not be *correct*. The fanatascism and insanity of the Japanese regime at that time cannot be taken lightly. The convinced thousands of civilians to commit suicide rather than be taken alive by the Americans. Despite being short of munitions and food, they fought on bitterly, causing severe casualties to the Allies. Even if Japan as a nation had surrendered, how many woudl *not* surrender and would have fought on to the death? Remember, the fanaticism was *extreme*, the Emperor was a God and the Japanese were not normal humans, but a blessed race--it was like religious fervour. Fanatacism and desperation made the Battle for Berlin carnage that the Western Allies never saw, but knew of, they did not want that on a much larger scale.<br>
