<br>
npb mate :)  unlike real life, we can't sit around having a gab, drinking, chewing food, swapping tales, and seeing the other person's face and understanding their emotions and sincerity better. Over the Net, it comes over very flat, so it's hard to get the nuances of people's meanings, you know? So we tend to get irate, me included ;) <br>
<br>
That's why I use smileys a lot, they are simplistic but easy clues to let the other person know moods, the &quot;mad grin smiley&quot;   <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-large;">: &gt;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->    is a bit of trademark of mine ;) <br>
<br>
British folk tend to let the listener finish things for themselves..<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Well, you know what HE is like....&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
